[Student "S"]
{The bidding has been as shown.   

This is one of the nicer parts of Negative Doubles. When the bidding is 1\C - 1\D, a double by you promises both Majors. It's like you are allowed to bid both suits at once, 1\S\H. So you double and partner says 1NT.  

Partner doesn't have 4 of either Major. But he does have 13 points and \Ds stopped. You also have 13 points so you bid 3NT.}

